<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>How to Choose the Right Size</h2>

  <p>
    Match the clip size to the diameter of your seedlings at the graft point. Clips that are slightly larger than the stem allow for growth without excessive pressure.
  </p>

  <p>
    Using multiple sizes can help if seedlings vary.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>How to Use Grafting Clips Properly</h2>

  <ol class="plainList">
    <li>Align the scion and rootstock carefully.</li>
    <li>Place the clip over the graft union.</li>
    <li>Ensure gentle but firm contact.</li>
    <li>Monitor for movement or stress.</li>
  </ol>

  <p>
    Stability during healing is critical.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>What Most Gardeners Get Wrong</h2>

  <h3>Using Clips That Are Too Tight</h3>
